00:01:34.810 --> 00:01:42.600
So your course objectives are to
get ready for your official FAA

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:44.820
Knowledge Test.

00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:47.880
This is sometimes called
the written test as opposed

00:01:47.880 --> 00:01:49.680
to the practical
test or the check

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:53.100
ride that you do at the end
of your flight training.

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:55.500
It's available in a bunch
of different versions,

00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:59.220
including for airplanes
and helicopters.

00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:02.550
We're going to concentrate in
this class on airplane, partly

00:02:02.550 --> 00:02:05.290
because of the show of hands.

00:02:05.290 --> 00:02:09.710
You will also be prepared though
for the FAA's remote pilot

00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:12.770
test, if you decide to go
direct entry into the world

00:02:12.770 --> 00:02:14.720
of commercial drones.

00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:17.930
We hope that this is
also going to help you.

00:02:17.930 --> 00:02:19.670
Any kind of thorough
study usually

00:02:19.670 --> 00:02:23.840
helps you make more efficient
use of your in-aircraft time.

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:28.460
And cause we have Tina here,
with her PhD in aero-astro,

00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:32.930
you're going to learn something
about the engineering as well.

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:37.220
So what is great about aviation?

00:02:37.220 --> 00:02:40.340
People were dreaming about
flying a long time ago going

00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:42.020
back to the ancient Greeks.

00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:46.580
Only recently, we've been able
to do it which is a good thing.

00:02:46.580 --> 00:02:49.190
One thing I like
about it is to look

00:02:49.190 --> 00:02:52.820
at the geology and
the organization

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.340
of human settlement
on the planet.

00:02:55.340 --> 00:02:57.260
It's a lot of interesting
structural patterns

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:02.410
that one can see from above.

00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:04.930
Flying, a lot of the greatest
engineering achievements

00:03:04.930 --> 00:03:10.510
of the last 100 years or so
are embodied in the aircraft

00:03:10.510 --> 00:03:15.080
that you can personally go
down to the local airport,

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:18.460
rent, and fly.

00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:23.230
Also, everybody at MIT is pretty
good at doing stuff at a desk

00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:27.580
and thinking about hard
problems when sitting at a desk,

00:03:27.580 --> 00:03:34.240
but there's no emotions to
manage other than depression.

00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:36.645
So flying combines everything.

00:03:36.645 --> 00:03:38.020
You might be a
little bit afraid.

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:40.180
It's not natural to
be up in the air.

00:03:40.180 --> 00:03:43.960
So you're working all of your
human capacities at one time.

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:46.690
You're managing your fear,
you're working your brain

00:03:46.690 --> 00:03:48.700
to think about
what's coming next,

00:03:48.700 --> 00:03:53.290
and you're also
working your muscles.

00:03:53.290 --> 00:03:57.100
Finally, you can get
to the beach quickly,

00:03:57.100 --> 00:04:00.748
but as I note here, most
places, unfortunately

00:04:00.748 --> 00:04:03.040
little airplanes when you
factor in the weather and all

00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:06.760
the training that you have
to do, a lot of times,

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:09.130
you could've gotten
door-to-door faster.

