If you were to drive, it would
be a 4 1/2 hour drive to get

00:08:18.810 --> 00:08:20.093
there and back.

00:08:20.093 --> 00:08:21.510
So it wouldn't
really be something

00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:24.210
that you could easily
do as a day trip,

00:08:24.210 --> 00:08:26.780
but since we were flying,
it was a great day trip.

00:08:26.780 --> 00:08:30.720
So we flew up along the coast
all the way to Bar Harbor,

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:32.370
and what was really
great about that

00:08:32.370 --> 00:08:33.750
is that we could go hiking.

00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:37.530
So all these folks flew
in little airplanes

00:08:37.530 --> 00:08:41.010
from the Boston area
through the MIT flying club,

00:08:41.010 --> 00:08:43.230
and we all flew up to
the Bar Harbor, Maine.

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:46.485
And then we went hiking in
the Acadia woods and forests,

00:08:46.485 --> 00:08:49.110
and it was really
beautiful, wonderful day,

00:08:49.110 --> 00:08:53.560
and then we flew back and landed
just after sunset back here.

00:08:53.560 --> 00:08:56.880
So it was a really beautiful
experience and a lot of fun

00:08:56.880 --> 00:08:59.260
to fly along the coastline.

00:08:59.260 --> 00:09:00.470
So I highly recommend it.

