AUDIENCE: An F-18.

00:12:48.630 --> 00:12:51.210
PROFESSOR 2: An F-18,
so what's really cool

00:12:51.210 --> 00:12:54.150
is that this airport
that I fly out of,

00:12:54.150 --> 00:12:58.320
Hanscom, is also a
military Air Force Base.

00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:01.150
Which is really exciting,
because upon occasion,

00:13:01.150 --> 00:13:03.900
you'll actually see
military jets come out.

00:13:03.900 --> 00:13:05.890
And they, of course,
did not wait for me,

00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:08.640
even though I was first in line.

00:13:08.640 --> 00:13:10.480
They nicely cut in front.

00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:14.460
They called themselves jet 1
and jet 2, and they went out.

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:16.380
And it really looked
like they didn't

00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:20.880
take any space at all, any of
the runway length to take off.

00:13:20.880 --> 00:13:24.300
It really looked, from where I
was sitting, right next to it,

00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:27.150
like they just turned like
a rocket ship and took off,

00:13:27.150 --> 00:13:30.820
and it was really amazing.

